# packages/ui (@repo/ui)

Read `.agents/skills/quoteflow/SKILL.md` before structural changes.

## Structure

```
src/screens/           # Full pages (login, dashboard, quotations, …)
src/components/layout/ # AppShell, AuthShell, auth-card-link
src/components/forms/  # TextField, SelectField, shared fields
src/components/ui/     # Gluestack primitives (+ index.web.tsx forks)
src/navigation/        # useNavigate, usePathname (abstracts Next router)
src/styles/globals.css # Tailwind + theme CSS variables
```

Types live in `@repo/types`. API integration lives in `@repo/api` (`packages/api/`).
Web passes env-specific config from `apps/web/lib/api-config.ts`.

## New screen checklist

1. Create `src/screens/<name>-screen.tsx` (`"use client"`)
2. Export path in `packages/ui/package.json` `"exports"`
3. Add thin route in `apps/web/app/.../page.tsx`
4. Use `@repo/ui` components - not raw `<div>` unless in `index.web.tsx`

## Data hooks

Screens use TanStack Query hooks (`useClients`, `useLogin`, …) from `@repo/api/hooks`. `ApiQueryProvider` is mounted from `apps/web/lib/providers.tsx`.
Screens stay unaware of HTTP - swap the provider implementation without touching UI.

## Layout

- `AppShell` - sidebar + header; use `flex-row` where horizontal
- `AuthShell` - split login/marketing layout
- `Box` defaults to **column** flex - always set `flex-row` when needed
